1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:09,280
I was pregnant, but I miscarried
because of an accident.

2
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:11,720
Now, think about it.

3
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:14,760
<i>Do you still want me</i>
<i>to come home with you?</i>

4
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:18,280
I'm sorry. I don't feel the same way.

5
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,240
<i>Pun still doesn't know</i>
<i>that I'm the guy in the picture.</i>

6
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:22,920
He asked, but I didn't tell him.

7
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:28,680
<i>What's in the past, let it go.</i>

8
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:33,600
We just have to brace ourselves
for what's coming next.

9
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,360
<i>Let's start fresh.</i>

10
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:38,120
I love you, Pie. Okay?

11
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:40,880
Oh, wow.

12
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:43,200
Her work is so detailed.

13
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,080
- Let me see the picture.
- Sure.

14
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:49,480
Oh my, seeing this
really makes me think of her.

15
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,400
- Uncle Dech.
- Yes?

16
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:55,360
Thank you so much for recommending
that I go see Grandma Khamman.

17
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,680
I've gathered
all the fabric information now.

18
00:02:57,760 --> 00:03:00,560
I'll make it into content and decide
how to tell the fabric's story,

19
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:02,240
then I'll bring it to you soon.

20
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:04,800
Pie.

21
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:07,240
There's no rush.

22
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:10,000
Studying fabric isn't easy.

23
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:13,160
It takes time thinking it through
and working on it.

24
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,760
Because the patterns on each fabric piece

25
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:18,040
are complex, with many layers.

26
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,480
It's like life, really.

27
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,800
Sometimes it's not simple.

28
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:24,760
But if you can see the bigger picture

29
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:27,320
and understand how the threads overlap,

30
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,200
you'll get it.

31
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:33,360
Then, what once seemed difficult
will become easy.

32
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:40,240
Thank you for the advice, Uncle Dech.

33
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,240
You're welcome.

34
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,560
Uncle!

35
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,000
I won't be homeless anymore.

36
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:51,280
Pun has allowed me
to stay at Aunt Nhun's house.

37
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:58,040
I told him about fixing the house,

38
00:03:58,120 --> 00:04:00,840
and that's why he said
we could stay at Aunt Nhun's place.

39
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:04,560
Stay as long as you need.

40
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:06,200
Our families have been close
for a long time.

41
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:08,560
If there's anything I can do to help,
I'm happy to.

42
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:13,600
Thank you so much for inviting us, Pun.

43
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,040
Well, but…

44
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:18,959
I'm a bit worried about imposing on Nhun.

45
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:22,000
Don't worry, Uncle.

46
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:23,880
She'll be more than happy to help.

47
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:33,360
Besides Nhun, I'm also worried about Pie.

48
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,920
Wait a minute.

49
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:39,480
What's this all about?

50
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,800
What's going on, Uncle Dech?

51
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,520
My house got damaged.

52
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:00,760
- Oh no!
- It was that day when the heavy rain

53
00:05:00,840 --> 00:05:02,480
and lightning struck the tree.

54
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,440
The tree fell and hit the roof,

55
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:06,120
- and the roof got damaged too.
- Oh my!

56
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,120
So, I had a contractor
come by to assess it.

57
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,360
He said it'll take
at least a month to fix.

58
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:12,840
Honestly,

59
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:17,640
it feels like this bad luck
is just draining my bank account.

60
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:19,480
I haven't even finished
fixing the old house.

61
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,560
Now I have to fix
the one I'm living in too.

62
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,240
It's so frustrating.

63
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:26,600
That's some serious bad luck.
How unfortunate.

64
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:28,120
It must be tough, right, Mink?

65
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,760
Yeah, Auntie.

66
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:32,800
Just packing to go to a hotel
took up the whole day.

67
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:35,400
- Oh dear.
- I haven't even found a hotel yet.

68
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:39,080
I told her to come stay at your house,

69
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:40,320
so she wouldn't have to rent a hotel.

70
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,320
But Uncle's worried about imposing.

71
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:46,000
Hey, why worry about that?

72
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:50,400
Well, I'm not really in any trouble.

73
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:53,040
I'm going on a tour to Egypt tomorrow.

74
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,400
By the time I get back,
the house should be fixed.

75
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:58,080
I'm just worried about her, though.

76
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:01,080
She's going to have to stay
in your house for a while.

77
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,120
He's worried about Pie, though.

78
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:13,240
Pie.

79
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:18,240
You're not uncomfortable

80
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:20,960
if Mink stays here, right?

81
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:24,040
What's there to be uncomfortable about?

82
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,680
We're in different houses.

83
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:28,040
And the important thing is,
I'm the homeowner.

84
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,760
Anyone who's not the homeowner
doesn't need to worry about it.

85
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:34,040
You don't have to feel bad about it,
and Mink doesn't either.

86
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,480
Stay with me as long as you need.

87
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,560
I'm happy to take care of you.

88
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:40,200
Thank you, Auntie.

89
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:41,840
Alright?

90
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,200
Mother's right.

91
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:46,480
Uncle, you don't need to feel bad.

92
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,600
I've not really been living here
from the start.

93
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:52,080
I'm just a resident, not the owner.

94
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,160
I'm going back to work now.

95
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:57,400
Pie.

96
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,840
Don't go yet.

97
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:07,920
Could you show Mink her room?

98
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,320
Even though you're not the homeowner,

99
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:17,800
can you help her as a friend?

100
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:19,640
Okay?

101
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,440
Let's go.

102
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,960
Thanks, my friend.

103
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,440
This is the room.

104
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:45,280
Take a look around. I'm going to work now.

105
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:49,400
It seems like your marriage
isn't very happy.

106
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,720
I've read that

107
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:55,320
a good couple should have
four things in common.

108
00:07:56,440 --> 00:08:00,840
Faith, morals, generosity, and wisdom.

109
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:05,120
You and Pun don't seem
to share any of those.

110
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,840
It'll be hard to make it work.

111
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:09,280
Can you explain each of those to me?

112
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:10,920
What do they mean?

113
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:14,080
- Well, it's…
- Dharma from Instagram?

114
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,560
You just scroll and repeat what you see.

115
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:21,080
I'm glad you've started
looking into Dharma.

116
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:23,160
But if you really want to improve,
why not try…

117
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:25,760
keeping the five precepts?

118
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:28,280
Especially the third one.

119
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:31,880
Maybe then you'll stop meddling
in others' families.

120
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,480
I'm warning you nicely, Pie.

121
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:41,960
I wouldn't interfere
if you could really make Pun happy.

122
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,559
But it's obvious you can't.

123
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:45,520
You really have an issue
with me, don't you?

124
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,920
Why, can't you ever lose to me?

125
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,040
I've never lost.

126
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:50,600
You lost in cheerleading, school,
and the parade's main position.

127
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:52,080
You even lost trying to win over Pun.

128
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:53,800
Hey, sorry, Mungmink,

129
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:57,160
for always beating you,
even though I'm worse in every way.

130
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:03,160
Okay, maybe that was true in the past.

131
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:06,720
But it's not anymore.

132
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:09,640
It's obvious Aunt Nhun isn't fond of you,

133
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:13,160
and Pun doesn't even pay attention to you.

134
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:15,600
Looks like your good luck's run out.

135
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:17,840
Sorry about that.

136
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:26,160
If putting me down makes you feel better,

137
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,360
go ahead and do what you want.

138
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:32,600
I'm used to my feelings
being trampled for a long time.

139
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:39,840
This is probably another thing
I'll beat you at, Mungmink.

140
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:44,000
Because I've never felt inferior.

141
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:48,760
Even if you try to step on me,
my emotional armor is way too strong.

142
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:02,000
Pun's bedroom is just around the corner.

143
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,960
If you want to sneak over
and see him, feel free.

144
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:11,160
This is another thing I won't care about
if you actually do it.

145
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:16,000
You're clearly not into the five precepts.

146
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,160
Pie, you!

147
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,720
- Uncle.
- Yes?

148
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:35,000
I need to discuss something
about the museum project.

149
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,880
Oh, sure.

150
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:41,440
I've gone over the venue
in detail again, and I think

151
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:44,840
the proposal the team gave me
doesn't fully meet the needs.

152
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:46,280
I want to redo everything.

153
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:47,320
Huh?

154
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,720
Redo everything?

155
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:51,000
Yes.

156
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:54,520
I'll have the team revise the design
as soon as possible.

157
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:57,760
I promise the fabric project
will be finished on schedule.

158
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:00,600
But I've seen it, and it looks fine to me.

159
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,520
It's just fine.

160
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:08,920
If you're okay with it,
we can stick to that design.

161
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:12,120
But I don't want to create
something that's just fine.

162
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:14,400
I'm committed to making
this a good project,

163
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:16,160
not just something that passes.

164
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,360
Please allow me
to redo the design completely.

165
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:21,000
I'll take full responsibility.

166
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:23,160
Alright.

167
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:26,360
If you think it will be better, go ahead.

168
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:28,280
- Okay?
- Thank you.

169
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:33,760
I'll excuse myself now.

170
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:44,280
Rok, call an urgent meeting
for Uncle Dech's museum team.

171
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:45,720
There's a problem with Win's design.

172
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,360
Get everyone here now.

173
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,280
What's going on?

174
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:12,080
Mr. Dech wants to redo the design.

175
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:14,080
Redo it?

176
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:17,040
You mean start from scratch?

177
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:22,120
He said the design you made is too plain.

178
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:25,400
He wants something more unique.

179
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:29,640
He wants the museum
to look grand and more interesting.

180
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:32,000
But the original design I made

181
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:34,320
was because he didn't want
to change the house much.

182
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:37,720
That's true, but after the last meeting,

183
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:39,160
Pun said he changed his mind.

184
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:44,600
It's normal for clients
to change their minds during a project.

185
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:45,880
They ask us to make changes,

186
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:48,040
so we make them.

187
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:50,560
I can make the changes, no problem,

188
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:52,440
but I don't get why the brief is changing.

189
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:55,640
- I want to talk to Mr. Dech first.
- Hey!

190
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:58,520
Wait a minute, Win.

191
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:01,000
Saying that makes me look bad.

192
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:03,200
It's like I'm not clear,

193
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:05,040
and my team doesn't get me.

194
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,120
I get you, but I don't get the client.

195
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,280
You don't need to understand!

196
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:12,120
Just do what I told you.
What's so hard about that?

197
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:27,760
Win, let's do this instead.

198
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:29,080
Let's make the changes first,

199
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:31,920
and if he's not happy,
we can talk about it again later.

200
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:38,760
But I'm the designer.

201
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:42,520
I got the first brief from the client,
so I need to understand them first.

202
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:46,280
I want to understand why the client
is requesting such drastic changes.

203
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:51,480
Is it your ego?
Can't you just make the changes?

204
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:52,440
I'm not being egoistic.

205
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:54,760
I can change it,
but I need to understand why.

206
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:56,920
The reasons have already been explained!

207
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,520
- Listen and drop the ego. It's clear.
- I'm not being egoistic!

208
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,840
I told you that already!

209
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:11,600
Alright, Win.

210
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:17,760
I don't want us fighting
over something pointless like this.

211
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:22,160
Let's call it.

212
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,040
You don't have to work on this anymore.

213
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:29,400
That's it.

214
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,480
I won't get into your business anymore.

215
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,360
I get it.

216
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,360
You graduated abroad,

217
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:44,360
now you're untouchable.

218
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:48,680
I'm not like that.

219
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:50,720
- You know me.
- I don't know anymore.

220
00:14:53,640 --> 00:14:55,800
Honestly, I'm starting to doubt

221
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,920
if you're still the same Win I knew.

222
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:04,240
Let's not argue.

223
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:07,960
You'll ruin your reputation.

224
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:15,520
Meeting's over.

225
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:02,920
Be honest.

226
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,480
Did you do this to mess with me?

227
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:06,080
Hey.

228
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,480
If the work isn't good, just admit it.

229
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:10,080
Don't change the subject.

230
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:11,400
If you think that way,

231
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:14,480
it means you're not accepting
that your work isn't good.

232
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:17,520
You're not accepting your untouchable ego.

233
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:19,440
How can I accept that, Pun?

234
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:22,520
I talked to Mr. Dech,
and he said it was fine, that he liked it.

235
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,840
And now you're saying this.

236
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:25,720
Are you saying I'm lying?

237
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:28,400
For what?

238
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:32,640
Are you sure this isn't because of Pie?

239
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:37,360
What if I say…

240
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,600
yes?

241
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:47,280
You seriously can't separate things.

242
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:49,520
If you're upset about that,
take it out on me.

243
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:51,320
Don't blame the work. It's not related.

244
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:55,960
Hey, you're really going there?

245
00:16:58,360 --> 00:16:59,640
I'm just kidding.

246
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:05,839
Who would do that to their little brother,
the one they grew up with?

247
00:17:08,839 --> 00:17:10,960
I'm not going to make you feel bad.

248
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:14,000
You know, since we were kids,

249
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,400
I've always had your back.

250
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:20,720
I've always warned you
about anything that could hurt you.

251
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:24,160
Even though you never warned me

252
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:27,079
that I was standing on a bomb.

253
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:39,400
Stop asking and go find a new job.

254
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,200
This industry is small.

255
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,720
If your reputation's bad,
everyone will know.

256
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:54,400
This is a warning, not a threat.

257
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:09,680
RECEIVED A TRANSFER OF 10,000 BAHT.

258
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:11,400
Why is it only 10,000?

259
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:13,360
PIE'S MOM

260
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,520
What's up, Mom?

261
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:24,720
Hello, Pun.

262
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:27,640
Well, I just checked the balance,

263
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:30,320
<i>and it only shows 10,000.</i>

264
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,240
Did you make a mistake with the transfer?

265
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,680
Normally, you don't just send me 10,000.

266
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:36,440
No mistake. I sent the right amount.

267
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:41,480
Hey, Pun, you usually send me 60,000.

268
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:45,280
Ten thousand isn't even enough
to cover my monthly expenses.

269
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:46,280
Mom.

270
00:18:47,320 --> 00:18:48,720
Are you serious, or are you lying?

271
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:50,400
I'm serious, Pun.

272
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,640
Why would you ask that?

273
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:55,840
Lately, I'm having trust issues.

274
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,480
I don't trust anyone.

275
00:18:57,560 --> 00:19:00,840
I just had someone I trusted
lie straight to my face.

276
00:19:00,920 --> 00:19:02,720
It wasn't just one person,

277
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:05,360
but the whole family was in on the lie.

278
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:07,320
<i>You should already know about this.</i>

279
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,680
So I don't need to explain further.

280
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:14,080
Pun, I'm sorry about that.

281
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:16,080
I can explain.

282
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:18,600
- It's just that--
- I have work to do.

283
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:20,960
I don't have time
to listen to your explanation.

284
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:24,320
Same goes for the money.
I won't have time to explain it to you.

285
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:28,560
From now on,
I can only transfer 10,000 baht to you.

286
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:31,320
<i>You already have a house,</i>
<i>a car, and money.</i>

287
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,840
You can take care of yourself
without my money.

288
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:35,680
Goodbye.

289
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:38,680
Wait, Pun! Hello?

290
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:42,360
You're hanging up already?

291
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:02,320
Auntie!

292
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:06,920
When did you get here?

293
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,560
I took the early flight.

294
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:12,160
I missed you, so I brought
lots of northern food!

295
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:16,080
Wait, what happened to your face?

296
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:19,200
It's a long story. I'll tell you later.

297
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:21,680
Come on, eat first.

298
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:23,520
I'll set it up for you.

299
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:27,560
<i>What?</i>

300
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:30,120
Pun knows the truth now?

301
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,320
What did he say about it?

302
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:33,760
He seemed off.

303
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:36,760
He said everything was okay,

304
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:39,400
but honestly, I don't think he's okay.

305
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:43,000
If I were him, I wouldn't be okay either.

306
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:45,680
If I were him, I'd probably
get a migraine from the stress.

307
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:50,360
Honestly, Auntie, I've never
seen Pun like this before.

308
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:58,920
If you're going through this,
won't Pie go through it too?

309
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:21,480
Hey, what's wrong?

310
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:24,800
Yesterday, Win broke my heart.

311
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:27,280
Then today, I saw him again.

312
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:31,720
I'm not okay, Pie. I can't move on yet.

313
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:48,000
Win said he didn't feel
the same way I did.

314
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,880
Then he apologized to me.

315
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:53,920
He was straightforward.
He didn't sugarcoat anything.

316
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,400
And he didn't give me any false hope.

317
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:59,920
Come on. Are you okay? Don't cry.

318
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,240
You'll meet someone new, right?

319
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:03,560
Okay?

320
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:05,200
I don't want someone new.

321
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:08,120
I like him. I want him.

322
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:19,560
- I'm going to keep going.
- Huh?

323
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:23,200
Pie, please cheer me on, okay?

324
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:26,080
I've never met anyone
who's right for me like this before.

325
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:29,680
This is the one who's perfect
for me in my life.

326
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:32,800
Oh my God, he's my number one!

327
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:33,960
Please, Pie!

328
00:22:37,280 --> 00:22:41,640
I want a good relationship.
I don't want to get hurt again.

329
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:48,080
Please!

330
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:53,720
Rok.

331
00:22:58,160 --> 00:23:00,440
There is something I've never told you.

332
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:08,400
But I think…

333
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,120
it's time I tell you.

334
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:27,400
Do you remember

335
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:30,400
when I went to Mae Hong Son
for my final project?

336
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,240
Of course I remember.

337
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:36,160
That's when you had me lie to your mom
about us going together.

338
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:39,800
Then your mom found out,
and we both got yelled at.

339
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:43,640
Yeah, that time.

340
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:47,800
Back then,

341
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:52,280
it wasn't just because I lied
about going alone.

342
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:00,800
I met someone in Mae Hong Son.

343
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:07,560
And we decided to become a couple.

344
00:24:08,120 --> 00:24:09,200
What?

345
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:12,320
- A couple?
- Yeah.

346
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:14,520
Wait, you've had a boyfriend?

347
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:18,320
Why didn't you tell me?

348
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:25,720
Or is it more than just a boyfriend?

349
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:29,800
I mean, your relationship
shouldn't be a secret.

350
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:30,880
Come on.

351
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:33,240
It's such a small thing.

352
00:24:33,320 --> 00:24:34,480
I know, but…

353
00:24:41,560 --> 00:24:43,440
I didn't want to blame my mom.

354
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:46,360
I was confused back then, Rok.

355
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:50,520
My mom told me to forget about it,
to not tell anyone.

356
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:52,880
And at that time, I trusted her.

357
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:56,240
So why are you telling me now?

358
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,600
What does it have to do with me?

359
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,600
Rok.

360
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:12,240
I should've told you a long time ago.

361
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:17,760
But I didn't think staying quiet
would complicate things this much.

362
00:25:24,560 --> 00:25:25,520
Rok.

363
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:33,160
I'm sorry.
I'm really sorry. It's my fault.

364
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:38,880
The person I used to date is…

365
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:47,760
Win.

366
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:54,200
Win?

367
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:57,640
The same Win?

368
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:03,320
Yeah.

369
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:11,360
<i>Here, this picture.</i>

370
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:13,320
But it's blurry, and his head is cut off,

371
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:15,800
so you didn't see how handsome he is.

372
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:18,800
Now you can see how handsome he is, right?

373
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:21,440
But he is good, you know.

374
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:24,200
I'm talking about his work, not his looks.

375
00:26:24,280 --> 00:26:26,000
He graduated from Japan, you know?

376
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:29,440
Whether he graduated from Japan
or anywhere else doesn't matter

377
00:26:29,520 --> 00:26:31,400
if he's not committed to working with us.

378
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:32,440
Isn't that right?

379
00:26:32,520 --> 00:26:34,480
Win's nice.

380
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:36,240
He's warm, like a microwave.

381
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:38,920
<i>Do you really know him well?</i>

382
00:26:39,480 --> 00:26:41,200
<i>He might not be as nice as you think.</i>

383
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:46,000
I sent a message to Win,
but he didn’t read it or reply.

384
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:47,440
What should I do?

385
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:49,440
<i>You're overthinking it.</i>

386
00:26:49,520 --> 00:26:51,440
<i>Just relax.</i>

387
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:56,960
Hey, seriously.

388
00:26:57,840 --> 00:26:59,080
I don't get it.

389
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:03,920
I don't know how serious this is
for your mom to stop you from talking.

390
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:08,760
But I'm your friend.

391
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:13,480
I tell you everything,
no matter how messed up it is.

392
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,280
After doing this to me,

393
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:20,000
are you still seeing me
as your friend, Pie?

394
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:22,560
Hey, don't talk like that.

395
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:34,680
I've always seen you as my friend.

396
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:38,600
You're my best friend, okay?

397
00:27:38,680 --> 00:27:40,440
Best friend? Really, Pie?

398
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:44,240
Is this how you treat your best friend?

399
00:27:46,040 --> 00:27:48,200
You're treating me like I'm stupid.

400
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:50,120
I came to you for advice,

401
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:53,960
like how I should fall in love,
how to date your ex.

402
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:58,080
And your ex kept quiet,
never saying anything about being your ex?

403
00:27:59,560 --> 00:28:01,080
Are you two making a fool out of me?

404
00:28:01,160 --> 00:28:04,320
Hey, that's not it.
I never thought like that.

405
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:07,080
Do you understand?

406
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:11,360
Once I lied about one thing,
I had to keep lying. I'm sorry.

407
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:13,360
Then why are you telling me now?

408
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:15,040
Why not just lie forever?

409
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:18,600
The lies I've been telling
are eating me alive, Rok.

410
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:26,200
I don't want to hide anything anymore.

411
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:27,720
I'm going to tell the truth.

412
00:28:28,600 --> 00:28:31,200
I already told Pun,
and now I'm telling you.

413
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:34,200
Rok…

414
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:38,040
You can be mad at me, hate me,
whatever, I get it.

415
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:41,160
I'm ready to face everything.

416
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:50,000
Now that you've said everything,
you must feel relieved, huh?

417
00:28:52,320 --> 00:28:54,160
But for me, now that I know the truth,

418
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:57,320
I'm so hurt.

419
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:02,120
You're so selfish.

420
00:29:58,240 --> 00:29:59,440
Rok!

421
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:01,800
What's wrong? Why are you crying?

422
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:04,680
What did Pie do to you?

423
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:06,640
Tell me, I'll go yell at her.

424
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:10,280
Wait, Rok! Where are you going?

425
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:12,520
Don't follow me, Mink.

426
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:55,440
WIN

427
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:15,800
Hello?

428
00:31:16,600 --> 00:31:18,680
How are you, Pie?

429
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:21,480
Rok came to see me today.

430
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,480
I told her everything.

431
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:27,440
She knows everything now.

432
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:31,280
It's time to tell the truth to everyone.

433
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:38,920
If you can't handle it, tell me.

434
00:31:42,080 --> 00:31:44,000
If I can help, I want to.

435
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:52,560
I started this problem.

436
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:55,160
So I have to fix it myself.

437
00:31:58,560 --> 00:31:59,760
But thank you so much.

438
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:32,280
<i>Prepare dinner too.</i>

439
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:34,480
<i>Haven't had food made by you in a while.</i>

440
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:36,520
<i>I miss it.</i>

441
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:09,040
Mink is going to stay with us?

442
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:11,040
Yeah.

443
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:13,280
Her house needs to be repaired,

444
00:33:13,360 --> 00:33:16,000
so I invited both her and her uncle
to stay here.

445
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:18,880
I'll be bothering you for a bit, Uncle.

446
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:20,560
No problem.

447
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:22,960
I'm sure the homeowner is happy with it.

448
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:27,120
How about you?

449
00:33:27,200 --> 00:33:29,080
Has staying silent
made you lose your voice?

450
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:31,720
It's just right.
This happens when you don't talk.

451
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:35,840
You haven't talked to anyone at all?

452
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:42,400
I thought you'd discuss dharma
with the monks or something.

453
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:44,680
Well, occasionally.

454
00:33:45,520 --> 00:33:46,480
Pun.

455
00:33:46,560 --> 00:33:48,080
Let Dad take a shower.

456
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:49,360
It's almost time for dinner.

457
00:33:49,440 --> 00:33:50,800
We can talk about dharma afterward.

458
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:52,320
Sure.

459
00:33:56,280 --> 00:33:58,280
Thanks for not telling Mom.

460
00:33:58,360 --> 00:34:01,840
I'm doing it for Mom, not for you.

461
00:34:24,239 --> 00:34:25,440
Ms. Pie.

462
00:34:26,280 --> 00:34:29,159
Mr. Pun asked me to tell you
to come eat at the main house.

463
00:34:30,520 --> 00:34:33,239
But he told me to make food, though.

464
00:34:33,320 --> 00:34:36,400
Are you sure that Pun and I
are supposed to eat over there?

465
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:37,639
Yes, I'm sure.

466
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:40,520
Everyone's waiting for you now.

467
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:52,199
While your uncle is on his Egypt tour,

468
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:55,040
how about we plan a trip together?

469
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:57,240
How about Europe, Auntie?
I'm good with that.

470
00:34:57,320 --> 00:35:00,120
Let me know the dates,
and I'll join if I can.

471
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:02,680
Great, a family trip then!

472
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:05,160
If you ditch us, Pun,
I'll really curse you.

473
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:06,680
Wait, Mink.

474
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:07,920
You'll curse me?

475
00:35:08,520 --> 00:35:09,600
And Uncle too.

476
00:35:11,280 --> 00:35:12,320
Yay!

477
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:15,640
Hey, Pie.

478
00:35:18,640 --> 00:35:20,760
Didn't you say Pie wasn't home?

479
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:28,720
I must have misunderstood.

480
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:31,960
Lately, she doesn't tell me much
about what she's up to.

481
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:34,520
Sometimes, I don't know the full story.

482
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:46,320
Then come sit, Pie. Let's eat.

483
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:48,680
We didn't wait. We've already started.

484
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:49,760
Come sit down.

485
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:54,000
Sit here.

486
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:59,160
Tian, please set a plate for Pie.

487
00:36:25,080 --> 00:36:27,680
Mink, did you get the food?

488
00:36:27,760 --> 00:36:29,440
Could you serve me some, Pun?

489
00:36:39,760 --> 00:36:40,760
Thank you.

490
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,440
I'll ask you straight.

491
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:15,360
When you said everything
was okay between us,

492
00:37:16,600 --> 00:37:18,640
the truth is, you weren't okay, right?

493
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:22,120
You want to get back at me, don't you?

494
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:29,680
Get back at you?

495
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:32,240
What do you mean?

496
00:37:32,320 --> 00:37:34,440
Get back at me
for not telling you about Win.

497
00:37:34,520 --> 00:37:36,600
That's such a small thing, Pie.

498
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:39,280
I'm not someone who holds grudges.

499
00:37:39,360 --> 00:37:40,600
Why would I get back at you?

500
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:43,600
Also,

501
00:37:45,080 --> 00:37:47,800
I'm not someone who doesn't understand.

502
00:37:47,880 --> 00:37:52,240
I know you had your reasons
for what you did.

503
00:37:53,560 --> 00:37:55,920
Right now, just understand

504
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:58,000
that I have my reasons

505
00:37:59,440 --> 00:38:00,920
for what I do too.

506
00:38:14,240 --> 00:38:15,480
Don't worry, okay?

507
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:19,120
I'm not a cruel person.

508
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:24,920
I just don't like
being taken advantage of.

509
00:38:38,040 --> 00:38:39,200
I'm tired now.

510
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:43,000
I need to rest.

511
00:39:16,040 --> 00:39:17,040
In the past,

512
00:39:18,840 --> 00:39:20,000
I might not have spoken up

513
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:22,280
and went along with everyone.

514
00:39:23,880 --> 00:39:25,640
And it's been proven that it didn't work.

515
00:39:28,080 --> 00:39:32,160
If you want to say one thing
and do another to get back at me,

516
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:35,280
if it makes you feel better, go ahead.

517
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:39,720
When everything is over…

518
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:43,680
I'll feel less guilty.

519
00:39:47,840 --> 00:39:49,080
Goodnight.

520
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:25,440
When a married couple
doesn't sleep together,

521
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:27,440
it's concerning, huh?

522
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:33,160
You can ask a friend like me for advice
on making up with your husband.

523
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:37,560
I'll handle family matters on my own.

524
00:40:38,560 --> 00:40:39,560
Outsiders

525
00:40:40,680 --> 00:40:41,800
won't understand.

526
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:44,960
Don't act all high and mighty with me.

527
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:48,280
Your husband doesn't want you,
and neither do your friends.

528
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:51,960
Everyone knows who you really are now.

529
00:40:52,680 --> 00:40:55,360
Just so you know,
you're about to have no one left.

530
00:41:04,760 --> 00:41:05,840
Yeah.

531
00:41:05,920 --> 00:41:10,520
If you don't stop talking badly to me,
you'll meet the real me too.

532
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:15,320
I've been letting it go,
but don't push me to lose my patience.

533
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:23,600
Oh no, Miss Mink!

534
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:58,520
MOM

535
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:04,560
- What's up, Mom?
- Did Pun say anything about money?

536
00:42:05,160 --> 00:42:06,040
What money?

537
00:42:06,680 --> 00:42:08,520
<i>My salary, of course.</i>

538
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:12,120
Pie, Pun usually gives me 60,000 a month.

539
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:15,960
<i>But now he only gave me 10,000.</i>
<i>How is that enough?</i>

540
00:42:16,040 --> 00:42:19,680
I think he's angry
and is taking it out on me.

541
00:42:19,760 --> 00:42:24,080
Out of nowhere, he starts talking
about not trusting and mentioning a liar.

542
00:42:24,680 --> 00:42:28,520
<i>Pie, and he also told me</i>
<i>to take care of myself.</i>

543
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:30,000
<i>That's crazy.</i>

544
00:42:30,080 --> 00:42:32,320
I haven't been able
to take care of myself for ages.

545
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:34,200
How am I supposed to do that?

546
00:42:34,960 --> 00:42:37,440
If Pun doesn't give me money,

547
00:42:37,520 --> 00:42:39,640
where am I supposed to get money
for household expenses?

548
00:42:40,320 --> 00:42:43,680
<i>Look at this. Everything's a mess!</i>

549
00:42:44,720 --> 00:42:47,040
I already told you, right?

550
00:42:47,120 --> 00:42:49,200
You shouldn't mention Win.

551
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:51,560
I've done the right thing, Mom.

552
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:54,680
We shouldn't have taken his money
in the first place.

553
00:42:54,760 --> 00:42:57,160
We've already taken enough
from him, Mom. It's enough now.

554
00:42:58,120 --> 00:43:01,920
And right now, he's not okay with me,
so his reaction makes sense.

555
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:03,240
<i>What do you mean, Pie?</i>

556
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:04,360
I don't care.

557
00:43:04,440 --> 00:43:06,680
Do whatever
you need to do to make him okay.

558
00:43:06,760 --> 00:43:08,880
<i>Go apologize to him,</i>
<i>or do whatever it takes</i>

559
00:43:08,960 --> 00:43:11,560
to make him stop being mad.

560
00:43:11,640 --> 00:43:13,000
Mom.

561
00:43:13,080 --> 00:43:15,720
If Pun is angry, that's his right.

562
00:43:17,440 --> 00:43:19,680
<i>It's time for us to accept the truth.</i>

563
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:21,880
This is the real me.

564
00:43:21,960 --> 00:43:25,200
If he can't accept it, then it's over.

565
00:43:25,280 --> 00:43:28,720
Over? Over with Pun?

566
00:43:28,800 --> 00:43:29,840
No way.

567
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:32,400
<i>I won't let you end things with him.</i>

568
00:43:33,680 --> 00:43:34,720
Pie!

569
00:44:32,160 --> 00:44:34,320
CERTIFICATE OF MARRIAGE

570
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:42,080
MR. PARIT PITTHAKORN
MS. PHITPICHA ATTWIJIT

571
00:44:47,480 --> 00:44:49,160
DOCUMENTS REQUIRED
FOR DIVORCE REGISTRATION

572
00:44:49,240 --> 00:44:51,080
STEPS FOR REGISTERING A DIVORCE

573
00:44:51,160 --> 00:44:53,000
STEPS FOR REGISTERING A DIVORCE

574
00:44:53,080 --> 00:44:54,760
DIVORCE REGISTRATION BY MUTUAL CONSENT

575
00:45:21,080 --> 00:45:21,920
Here.

576
00:45:24,480 --> 00:45:25,960
You're worried about Pie, right?

577
00:45:31,680 --> 00:45:32,960
If I hadn't come back,

578
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:36,440
Pie and Pun wouldn't be like this.

579
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:42,280
I'm really bad luck for her.

580
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:46,360
Have you ever heard this saying?

581
00:45:47,440 --> 00:45:49,760
Karma reveals intention.

582
00:45:50,360 --> 00:45:52,600
Karma can be both good and bad.

583
00:45:54,080 --> 00:45:58,440
A person's intention
is what shows whether it's good or bad.

584
00:45:59,280 --> 00:46:03,600
Neither you nor Pie intended to hurt Pun.

585
00:46:04,720 --> 00:46:06,800
She kept the past hidden
because she loves her mom.

586
00:46:06,880 --> 00:46:10,000
And you didn't speak up
because you love her.

587
00:46:11,080 --> 00:46:13,880
So both you and Pie did this out of love.

588
00:46:17,640 --> 00:46:20,520
No one wanted to hurt Pun.

589
00:46:20,600 --> 00:46:22,600
But he is still hurt.

590
00:46:25,720 --> 00:46:27,680
He probably doesn't care
about our intentions.

591
00:46:28,240 --> 00:46:30,320
Some things are gray, you know.

592
00:46:30,400 --> 00:46:32,760
You can't always tell
what's right or wrong.

593
00:46:33,520 --> 00:46:35,240
Right now, Pun is angry.

594
00:46:35,920 --> 00:46:37,800
He won't listen to any reasoning.

595
00:46:39,160 --> 00:46:41,400
Just give it some time.

596
00:46:41,480 --> 00:46:45,040
Let the situation calm down. I think…

597
00:46:46,400 --> 00:46:47,880
Pun might eventually listen.

598
00:46:55,800 --> 00:46:57,600
That day might never come, though.

599
00:47:23,760 --> 00:47:25,440
The proposal I submitted didn't pass?

600
00:47:25,960 --> 00:47:29,160
But last time,
you said it wasn't an issue.

601
00:47:29,240 --> 00:47:34,880
Well, a senior I know
offered to help with the design.

602
00:47:34,960 --> 00:47:38,560
They'll only charge half
of what you requested for the costs.

603
00:47:39,160 --> 00:47:41,280
Since the museum's budget is tight,

604
00:47:41,360 --> 00:47:44,160
I decided to have this senior do it.

605
00:47:44,240 --> 00:47:46,600
Who's this senior you're talking about?

606
00:47:47,240 --> 00:47:48,120
You know him.

607
00:47:49,560 --> 00:47:52,200
- Pun?
- Yeah.

608
00:47:53,240 --> 00:47:54,640
<i>Why was my project canceled?</i>

609
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:57,080
Pun proposed a lower budget

610
00:47:57,160 --> 00:47:59,400
and offered to oversee the project.

611
00:47:59,480 --> 00:48:01,760
With him helping out, the client is happy.

612
00:48:01,840 --> 00:48:03,760
I gave the project to someone else.

613
00:48:06,240 --> 00:48:07,840
We've got Pun's company handling it now.

614
00:48:07,920 --> 00:48:09,360
Maybe next time, Win.

615
00:48:09,440 --> 00:48:10,400
Maybe next time, Win.

616
00:48:14,680 --> 00:48:17,160
Win! Today, Pun doesn't want anyone
to meet with him.

617
00:48:17,240 --> 00:48:18,320
Win!

618
00:48:24,680 --> 00:48:25,800
Get out.

619
00:48:32,680 --> 00:48:34,440
The five companies
I submitted proposals to

620
00:48:34,520 --> 00:48:36,680
were rejected
because you undercut the price.

621
00:48:36,760 --> 00:48:38,120
Then you kicked me out.

622
00:48:39,360 --> 00:48:41,280
If this is your way of getting back at me,

623
00:48:41,360 --> 00:48:44,080
I'm happy for you that you succeeded.

624
00:48:44,160 --> 00:48:46,040
If it makes you feel better,

625
00:48:46,120 --> 00:48:47,440
I'm okay with it.

626
00:48:48,600 --> 00:48:49,480
Hey.

627
00:48:50,120 --> 00:48:51,560
What are you talking about?

628
00:48:52,840 --> 00:48:55,040
I accepted the job following the process.

629
00:48:55,120 --> 00:48:57,400
I didn't force them to choose me.

630
00:48:58,040 --> 00:49:00,400
They just chose the better option.

631
00:49:00,480 --> 00:49:03,000
If you want them to choose you,
act like someone worth choosing.

632
00:49:03,080 --> 00:49:05,800
You can make any excuse you want,
but I don't care anymore.

633
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:09,040
Hey, don't snap at me.

634
00:49:10,320 --> 00:49:12,920
We can talk. Just say it directly.

635
00:49:13,000 --> 00:49:15,400
I'm open-minded.

636
00:49:15,480 --> 00:49:16,920
You can speak your mind.

637
00:49:23,640 --> 00:49:25,240
But someone like you
probably can't do that.

638
00:49:28,160 --> 00:49:31,480
In the past, with really important things
you should have said,

639
00:49:31,560 --> 00:49:32,960
you didn't!

640
00:49:33,040 --> 00:49:34,960
You chose to keep things hidden.

641
00:49:35,040 --> 00:49:37,720
Now, if you want to be honest
and speak directly,

642
00:49:38,600 --> 00:49:40,040
I bet you don't know how.

643
00:49:44,040 --> 00:49:47,880
The things I've kept from you,
I've already explained.

644
00:49:48,400 --> 00:49:50,160
As for the work,

645
00:49:50,240 --> 00:49:53,800
if me losing my place,
my job, and my future

646
00:49:53,880 --> 00:49:55,600
makes you happy and satisfied,

647
00:49:55,680 --> 00:49:57,520
then go ahead, feel free.

648
00:49:57,600 --> 00:49:59,520
I've got nothing left in my life anyway.

649
00:50:01,800 --> 00:50:05,240
Hey, this is getting way too dramatic.

650
00:50:09,760 --> 00:50:11,040
I was just joking.

651
00:50:13,400 --> 00:50:15,760
I haven't even really started
anything yet.

652
00:50:19,040 --> 00:50:22,160
What's the fun in getting back at someone
who doesn't care about their life?

653
00:50:27,720 --> 00:50:28,680
If I were to do something,

654
00:50:30,400 --> 00:50:32,800
it'd be with someone you care about,
and that would hurt more.

655
00:50:32,880 --> 00:50:34,600
What are you going to do to Pie?

656
00:50:35,840 --> 00:50:38,240
I haven't said anything about her.

657
00:50:39,160 --> 00:50:40,480
You admitted yourself

658
00:50:41,760 --> 00:50:43,880
that the person you care about is my wife!

659
00:50:44,960 --> 00:50:46,920
Should I be happy

660
00:50:47,640 --> 00:50:49,720
that you care this much about her?

661
00:50:49,800 --> 00:50:52,240
It's not about whether
she is your wife or not.

662
00:50:52,320 --> 00:50:53,680
Pie is a person.

663
00:50:55,560 --> 00:50:58,880
If you hurt Pie, I won't just stand by.

664
00:51:40,760 --> 00:51:43,240
I never thought Pun would go this far.

665
00:51:43,320 --> 00:51:45,360
No matter how hard he goes,
I'm ready to take it.

666
00:51:45,440 --> 00:51:47,440
But I'm worried he'll take it out on Pie.

667
00:51:49,120 --> 00:51:50,160
Is it just a threat?

668
00:51:50,240 --> 00:51:52,840
Would someone like him hurt his wife?

669
00:51:53,440 --> 00:51:54,920
Someone like him doesn't just threaten.

670
00:51:56,000 --> 00:51:57,160
He'll definitely do it.

671
00:51:59,480 --> 00:52:01,920
PIE

672
00:52:29,920 --> 00:52:31,840
Hey, wait a minute.

673
00:52:32,680 --> 00:52:34,440
We need to separate this into two things.

674
00:52:34,520 --> 00:52:37,720
First, the friend issue,
and second, the guy issue.

675
00:52:37,800 --> 00:52:39,760
You're upset with your friend

676
00:52:39,840 --> 00:52:45,280
because she never told you
she was dating the guy you liked.

677
00:52:46,480 --> 00:52:48,640
Now, I want you to close your eyes.

678
00:52:49,840 --> 00:52:50,760
Yeah.

679
00:52:50,840 --> 00:52:53,920
And imagine what I'm about to say.

680
00:52:54,000 --> 00:52:58,400
If this guy had accepted your love

681
00:52:59,000 --> 00:53:01,000
without ever breaking your heart,

682
00:53:01,080 --> 00:53:04,600
and now you're living a happy life,

683
00:53:05,320 --> 00:53:08,160
then Pie confesses the truth to you,

684
00:53:08,760 --> 00:53:11,440
would you be angry with her? Answer me.

685
00:53:12,480 --> 00:53:13,840
Isn't it hard to answer, Dad?

686
00:53:13,920 --> 00:53:15,880
Since the truth is I was dumped.

687
00:53:15,960 --> 00:53:19,120
I asked you to imagine,
not think about the truth.

688
00:53:19,200 --> 00:53:21,440
Would you be mad at Pie?

689
00:53:21,520 --> 00:53:23,000
Think about it.

690
00:53:25,320 --> 00:53:27,000
I'd be mad. I'd be mad for sure.

691
00:53:27,080 --> 00:53:29,080
When my best friend lies and betrays me,

692
00:53:29,160 --> 00:53:30,760
how can I not be mad, Dad?

693
00:53:38,480 --> 00:53:40,920
Alright.

694
00:53:41,000 --> 00:53:43,520
Let's think about it differently.

695
00:53:43,600 --> 00:53:45,160
Imagine this.

696
00:53:45,240 --> 00:53:47,160
What if Mink liked Win

697
00:53:47,920 --> 00:53:49,440
and Pie never told her

698
00:53:49,520 --> 00:53:52,320
that she had been Win's ex,
then Mink confessed her love…

699
00:53:52,400 --> 00:53:53,640
But I didn't confess my love.

700
00:53:53,720 --> 00:53:56,520
Hey, don't interrupt. I know.

701
00:53:57,120 --> 00:54:01,200
Just imagine what I'm saying.
Don't go off-topic.

702
00:54:01,280 --> 00:54:04,880
Mink gets her heart broken by Win,
and then Pie tells her the truth.

703
00:54:04,960 --> 00:54:06,320
Mink gets really mad.

704
00:54:06,400 --> 00:54:08,200
She starts yelling at you and Pie.

705
00:54:08,280 --> 00:54:12,320
She yells so loudly, really harshly,
until you can't take it anymore and says…

706
00:54:12,400 --> 00:54:13,880
So why are you mad at Pie?

707
00:54:13,960 --> 00:54:15,360
- Exactly!
- Exactly!

708
00:54:15,960 --> 00:54:16,920
You're right.

709
00:54:17,800 --> 00:54:19,640
Why would Mink be mad at Pie?

710
00:54:19,720 --> 00:54:21,720
If Pie didn't tell her, it means

711
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:24,720
there's probably
a really important reason for it.

712
00:54:29,760 --> 00:54:31,520
But you're angry

713
00:54:31,600 --> 00:54:34,600
because you're seeing everything
from your own perspective.

714
00:54:34,680 --> 00:54:38,360
You're judging from your perspective,
so everything they do seems wrong.

715
00:54:42,400 --> 00:54:45,360
Just like now, when you step back,

716
00:54:45,440 --> 00:54:47,000
you can see another side of it.

717
00:54:47,800 --> 00:54:50,440
You'll see it
from a friend's point of view,

718
00:54:50,520 --> 00:54:52,160
someone who loves
and is willing to understand their friend.

719
00:54:52,240 --> 00:54:53,600
Right, dear?

720
00:54:56,440 --> 00:54:59,360
Since you've known Pie, aside from this,

721
00:54:59,440 --> 00:55:02,000
has she ever made you upset?

722
00:55:02,080 --> 00:55:07,600
If not, is losing a friend over a guy
really worth it?

723
00:55:08,720 --> 00:55:12,560
And also,
everyone has their private matters.

724
00:55:12,640 --> 00:55:15,240
No matter how close we are,
it doesn't matter.

725
00:55:15,320 --> 00:55:17,880
They might have something personal
they don't want to share.

726
00:55:17,960 --> 00:55:20,920
Exactly. I even have things
I don't want to tell your dad.

727
00:55:21,000 --> 00:55:21,960
- Really?
- Of course.

728
00:55:22,040 --> 00:55:24,080
Well, there has to be some things, right?

729
00:55:24,160 --> 00:55:26,280
But I have my reasons.

730
00:55:26,360 --> 00:55:29,080
And I think Pie has her reasons too.

731
00:55:29,680 --> 00:55:33,640
Just because she didn't tell you
doesn't mean she wanted to hurt you.

732
00:55:34,440 --> 00:55:38,760
The person who's hurting
the most right now might be Pie.

733
00:55:42,600 --> 00:55:46,400
You said Pun is targeting Win.

734
00:55:46,480 --> 00:55:49,760
Do you think Pie will get hurt too?

735
00:55:49,840 --> 00:55:51,160
Think about it.

736
00:56:05,240 --> 00:56:09,120
CERTIFICATE OF MARRIAGE

737
00:56:19,000 --> 00:56:20,320
Let's get a divorce.

738
00:56:20,400 --> 00:56:22,000
I'm not ending this easily.

739
00:56:22,080 --> 00:56:24,360
I've already said everything to Pun.

740
00:56:24,440 --> 00:56:25,840
It's over.

741
00:56:27,000 --> 00:56:28,520
But I won't let it end!

742
00:56:29,200 --> 00:56:32,760
Don't let something
from your past with Win ruin everything.

743
00:56:32,840 --> 00:56:34,920
How hard is it to just say…

744
00:56:36,880 --> 00:56:38,240
if you love me or not?!

745
00:56:42,640 --> 00:56:44,720
You really want to die, don't you?!

746
00:56:44,800 --> 00:56:46,760
Pun! Stop!

747
00:56:46,840 --> 00:56:48,600
No! Let go!

748
00:57:22,880 --> 00:57:25,360
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
